(52, 2, 13, 60, 1, 23, 23, 'the word of God', 'Connection of God''s Word', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of the word of God in the believer''s life. 1 Thessalonians highlights its effectual working, while 1 Peter speaks of being born again by this enduring word.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 13, 60, 2, 2, 2, 'the word of God', 'Desire for the Word of God', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of receiving and desiring the word of God. 1 Thessalonians highlights the transformative power of the word, while 1 Peter encourages believers to crave it for spiritual growth.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 13, 42, 11, 28, 28, 'the word of God', 'Hearing and Keeping God''s Word', 'This connection highlights the importance of receiving and acting upon the word of God. Both passages emphasize the necessity of not only hearing the word but also keeping it, indicating a deeper engagement with divine truth.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 13, 44, 13, 48, 48, 'the word of God', 'Connection of Belief and Word', 'Both passages emphasize the reception of the word of God leading to belief. In 1 Thessalonians, believers accept the word as truth, while in Acts, those ordained to eternal life believe upon hearing it.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 13, 44, 17, 11, 11, 'received the word of God', 'Reception of the Word', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of receiving the word of God. In 1 Thessalonians, the believers accepted it as the truth, while in Acts, the Bereans received it with readiness and examined the scriptures.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 14, 52, 3, 4, 4, 'suffered like things of your own countrymen', 'Connection of Suffering in Thessalonians', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of suffering faced by the believers. In 1 Thessalonians 2:14, the suffering of the Thessalonians is compared to that of the churches in Judea, while 1 Thessalonians 3:4 recalls a prior warning about tribulation.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 14, 58, 5, 7, 8, 'suffered like things of your own countrymen', 'Suffering and Obedience Connection', 'Both passages emphasize suffering as a means of growth. In 1 Thessalonians, the believers suffer like those in Judea, while Hebrews highlights how Jesus learned obedience through suffering.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 14, 58, 10, 33, 34, 'suffered like things of your own countrymen', 'Suffering and Companionship in Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of suffering endured by believers and their solidarity with one another. In 1 Thessalonians, the suffering is linked to their countrymen, while Hebrews highlights the shared experiences of reproaches and afflictions.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 14, 53, 1, 4, 4, 'suffered like things of your own countrymen', 'Connection of Suffering and Endurance', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of suffering and endurance among believers. They highlight the shared experiences of persecution faced by the churches of God.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 14, 48, 1, 22, 22, NULL, 'Connection of Churches in Judea', 'Both passages emphasize the churches of Judea which were in Christ. This connection highlights the shared experience of suffering among these communities.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 14, 47, 8, 1, 2, 'suffered like things of your own countrymen', 'Suffering and Generosity Theme', 'Both passages emphasize suffering and its impact on the community. The churches in Judea and Macedonia experienced trials yet responded with joy and generosity, highlighting resilience in adversity.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 14, 44, 12, 1, 3, 'suffered like things of your own countrymen', 'Persecution of the Church', 'Both passages emphasize the suffering of the church. In 1 Thessalonians, the believers suffered from their countrymen, paralleling the persecution faced by the church in Acts, specifically from Herod and the Jews.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 15, 40, 5, 12, 12, 'persecuted us', 'Persecution of Prophets Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the persecution of prophets, highlighting a continuity in the suffering faced by God''s messengers. The mention of persecuting prophets in Matthew connects directly to the acknowledgment of those who killed the prophets in 1 Thessalonians.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 15, 42, 11, 48, 53, 'killed the Lord Jesus, and their own prophets', 'Connection of Persecution and Prophets', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of killing prophets and persecution. 1 Thessalonians mentions those who ''killed the Lord Jesus, and their own prophets,'' while Luke highlights the actions of those who ''killed them'' and ''persecuted'' prophets sent by God.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 15, 44, 2, 23, 23, 'killed the Lord Jesus', 'Connection of Persecution and Death', 'Both passages emphasize the act of killing Jesus and the role of wicked hands in this act. They highlight the persecution faced by Jesus and His followers, linking the actions of those who opposed them.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 15, 44, 7, 52, 52, 'killed the Lord Jesus', 'Persecution of Prophets and Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the persecution of prophets and the killing of Jesus. They highlight a pattern of rejection and violence against God''s messengers, culminating in the betrayal of Christ.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 15, 42, 13, 33, 34, 'killed the Lord Jesus, and their own prophets', 'Persecution of Prophets Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of killing prophets. 1 Thessalonians mentions those who ''killed the Lord Jesus, and their own prophets,'' while Luke highlights Jerusalem''s history of killing prophets.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 15, 40, 23, 31, 35, 'killed the Lord Jesus, and their own prophets', 'Connection of Persecution and Violence', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of killing prophets and persecution. 1 Thessalonians mentions those who killed the Lord Jesus and prophets, while Matthew directly addresses those who are the children of those who killed the prophets.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 15, 17, 3, 8, 8, 'persecuted us', 'Persecution of God''s People', 'Both passages emphasize the persecution of a specific people who are seen as contrary to the prevailing authority. In 1 Thessalonians, the focus is on those who killed Jesus and persecuted the apostles, while Esther highlights Haman''s plot against the Jews, who do not conform to the king''s laws.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 16, 44, 17, 13, 13, 'forbidding us to speak to the Gentiles', 'Opposition to Paul''s Ministry', 'This connection highlights the opposition Paul faced from the Jews in Thessalonica, as mentioned in both passages. In 1 Thessalonians, the Jews are described as forbidding the preaching to Gentiles, while Acts shows them actively stirring up the people against Paul.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 16, 44, 14, 19, 19, 'forbidding us to speak to the Gentiles', 'Persecution of Paul and Gentiles', 'Both passages emphasize the opposition faced by Paul in his mission to the Gentiles. In 1 Thessalonians, the Jews are depicted as forbidding the apostles from speaking to the Gentiles, while in Acts, certain Jews actively persecute Paul, leading to his stoning.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 16, 40, 23, 32, 32, 'fill up their sins alway', 'Connection of Wrath and Fulfillment', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of filling up sins or measures, suggesting a completion of wrongdoing leading to divine judgment. The phrase ''fill up'' in both contexts indicates a culmination of actions that provoke wrath.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 16, 41, 16, 16, 16, 'that they might be saved', 'Salvation and Belief Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of belief for salvation. In 1 Thessalonians, the warning against hindering the Gentiles'' salvation connects to the call for belief in Mark. This connection highlights the urgency of faith in the context of salvation.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 16, 39, 4, 1, 1, 'the wrath is come upon them', 'Judgment and Wrath Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the impending judgment and wrath against the wicked. In 1 Thessalonians, the ''wrath'' is directed towards those who oppose salvation, while Malachi describes a day of burning for the proud and wicked.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 16, 40, 21, 41, 44, 'the wrath is come upon them', 'Judgment and Rejection Themes', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment against those who reject God''s message. Both passages emphasize the consequences of rejecting God''s call, leading to the transfer of blessings to others.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 16, 48, 5, 11, 11, 'to fill up their sins alway', 'Persecution and Salvation Themes', 'This connection highlights the theme of persecution faced by those preaching salvation to the Gentiles. Both passages emphasize the consequences of opposing the message of the cross and the urgency of salvation.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 17, 51, 2, 5, 5, 'not in heart', 'Connection of Spiritual Presence', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of being present in spirit despite physical absence. This connection highlights the deep emotional bond and concern for the faith of the recipients.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 17, 46, 5, 3, 3, NULL, 'Presence in Spirit Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of being ''absent in body'' yet ''present in spirit.'' Both passages express a longing for connection despite physical separation, emphasizing emotional and spiritual presence.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 17, 52, 3, 6, 6, NULL, 'Desire to See Each Other', 'Both passages emphasize a strong desire to see one another. In 1 Thessalonians 2:17, the author expresses a longing to see the recipients, which is echoed in 1 Thessalonians 3:6 when Timothy reports that the recipients also desire to see the author.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 17, 45, 1, 13, 13, 'great desire', 'Desire for Fellowship', 'Both passages emphasize a strong desire to see fellow believers. In 1 Thessalonians, the author expresses a longing to see the Thessalonians, while in Romans, there is a similar intention to visit the Roman church.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 17, 10, 13, 39, 39, NULL, 'Longing for Connection', 'This connection highlights a deep longing for presence and reconciliation. Both passages emphasize the desire to be close to loved ones despite physical separation or loss.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 17, 19, 63, 1, 1, 'great desire', 'Desire for Connection', 'This connection highlights a deep longing for presence and communion. Both passages emphasize a thirsting for connection, whether with God or fellow believers.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 17, 42, 22, 15, 15, 'great desire', 'Desire for Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of deep desire for fellowship. Both passages emphasize a longing to be together, whether in presence or sharing a significant meal.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 18, 45, 15, 22, 22, 'hindered', 'Hindrance to Paul''s Visits', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being hindered from visiting. In 1 Thessalonians, Paul explicitly states that ''Satan hindered us,'' while in Romans, he notes he has been ''much hindered from coming to you.'' This connection highlights the challenges faced by Paul in his ministry.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 18, 45, 1, 13, 13, NULL, 'Obstacles to Paul''s Visits', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s desire to visit believers but highlight obstacles he faced. In 1 Thessalonians, he mentions being hindered by Satan, while in Romans, he notes being prevented from coming. This connection highlights the challenges Paul encountered in his ministry.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 18, 66, 2, 10, 10, 'Satan hindered us', 'Satan''s Hindrance and Suffering', 'This connection highlights the role of Satan in hindering believers'' efforts and causing suffering. Both passages emphasize the trials faced by Christians, with Satan actively opposing their faith and leading to tribulation.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 18, 38, 3, 1, 2, 'Satan hindered us', 'Resistance by Satan', 'This connection highlights the theme of Satan''s opposition in both passages. In 1 Thessalonians, Paul mentions how ''Satan hindered us,'' while in Zechariah, Satan stands to ''resist him,'' illustrating a consistent portrayal of Satan as an adversary.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 18, 18, 33, 14, 14, 'hindered us', 'Divine Communication and Human Perception', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine communication being hindered or unrecognized. In 1 Thessalonians, Paul notes that ''Satan hindered us,'' while Job emphasizes that ''man perceiveth it not.''', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 18, 47, 11, 12, 14, 'Satan hindered us', 'Satan''s Role in Hindrance', 'Both passages emphasize the influence of Satan in hindering the work of believers. In 1 Thessalonians, Paul mentions how ''Satan hindered us,'' while in 2 Corinthians, he describes Satan''s deceptive nature, indicating a broader theme of spiritual opposition.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 18, 40, 4, 10, 10, 'Satan hindered us', 'Satan''s Hindrance and Temptation', 'This connection highlights the role of Satan as an adversary in both passages. In 1 Thessalonians, Satan is depicted as hindering Paul''s efforts, while in Matthew, Jesus directly confronts Satan''s temptation, emphasizing the ongoing struggle against his influence.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 19, 50, 4, 1, 1, NULL, 'Joy and Crown Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concepts of joy and crown, linking the believers'' presence and steadfastness in the Lord to their ultimate reward at Christ''s coming. This connection highlights the communal aspect of faith and the joy derived from spiritual relationships.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 19, 52, 3, 13, 13, 'at his coming', 'Connection of Christ''s Coming', 'Both passages emphasize the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ, linking the hope and joy of believers with their holiness at His return. This connection highlights the anticipation of being in His presence.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 19, 50, 2, 16, 16, NULL, 'Joy and Rejoicing at Christ''s Coming', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of rejoicing in the presence of Christ. They reflect the hope and joy that believers have regarding the day of Christ''s return and the fulfillment of their labor.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 19, 47, 1, 14, 14, NULL, 'Rejoicing at Christ''s Coming', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of rejoicing in the presence of the Lord Jesus at His coming. They highlight the mutual joy and recognition between Paul and the believers, indicating a shared hope in the day of the Lord.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 19, 52, 5, 23, 23, NULL, 'Connection of Christ''s Coming', 'This connection highlights the anticipation of the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ in both passages. The first verse speaks of joy and hope at His coming, while the second emphasizes being preserved blameless until that same coming.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 19, 40, 16, 27, 27, 'in the presence of our Lord Jesus Christ', 'Connection of Christ''s Coming and Reward', 'Both passages emphasize the coming of the Lord and the rewards associated with it. 1 Thessalonians speaks of being in the presence of Christ at his coming, while Matthew highlights the rewarding of individuals according to their works at that same coming.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 19, 46, 15, 23, 23, 'at his coming', 'Connection of Christ''s Coming', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of Christ''s coming. 1 Thessalonians speaks of believers being in His presence, while 1 Corinthians refers to those who belong to Christ at His coming.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 20, 47, 1, 14, 14, 'our glory and joy', 'Connection of Joy and Rejoicing', 'Both passages emphasize the joy and rejoicing that believers share in their relationships with each other. The expressions of glory and joy in 1 Thessalonians parallel the acknowledgment of rejoicing in 2 Corinthians, highlighting mutual encouragement in faith.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 20, 46, 11, 7, 7, 'our glory', 'Glory and Joy Connection', 'This connection highlights the concept of ''glory'' in both passages. In 1 Thessalonians, believers are described as the ''glory'' of Paul and his companions, while in 1 Corinthians, man is referred to as the ''glory of God.'' Both passages emphasize the significance of glory in relation to identity.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 2, 20, 20, 17, 6, 6, 'our glory and joy', 'Glory and Joy in Relationships', 'This connection highlights the theme of familial relationships and the joy they bring. Both passages emphasize the glory derived from children and their connection to parents or elders.', 'theme', 0.3, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
