(52, 3, 1, 52, 3, 5, 5, 'could no longer forbear', 'Connection of Forbearance and Concern', 'Both passages emphasize the phrase ''could no longer forbear,'' highlighting Paul''s deep concern for the faith of the Thessalonians. This connection illustrates his emotional struggle and desire to ensure their spiritual well-being.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 3, 1, 52, 2, 17, 17, NULL, 'Longing for Presence', 'Both passages emphasize a deep desire for connection despite physical separation. In 1 Thessalonians 3:1, the longing to see the Thessalonians is evident, paralleling the sentiment in 1 Thessalonians 2:17 of being taken from them ''for a short time in presence, not in heart.''', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 3, 1, 24, 20, 9, 9, NULL, 'Connection of Forbearing and Speaking', 'Both passages emphasize the struggle of forbearing and the compulsion to speak. In 1 Thessalonians, the inability to forbear leads to action, while in Jeremiah, the burning desire to speak God''s word reflects a similar tension.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 3, 1, 47, 2, 13, 13, 'we could no longer forbear', 'Concern for Brothers in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the emotional distress of the authors due to the absence of their companions. In 1 Thessalonians, the concern leads to being left alone, while in 2 Corinthians, the lack of Titus causes unrest in spirit.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 3, 1, 24, 44, 22, 22, 'could no longer forbear', 'Connection of Forbearance and Evil', 'This connection highlights the theme of forbearance in both passages. In 1 Thessalonians, the inability to forbear reflects a response to distress, while in Jeremiah, the Lord''s inability to bear the evil of the people leads to desolation.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 3, 1, 47, 11, 29, 30, 'we could no longer forbear', 'Connection of Weakness and Infirmities', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of personal weakness and the emotional burden it brings. In 1 Thessalonians, the feeling of being left alone suggests vulnerability, while in 2 Corinthians, the acknowledgment of infirmities highlights a shared human experience of weakness.', 'theme', 0.293, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 3, 2, 44, 14, 22, 23, 'to establish you, and to comfort you', 'Encouragement in Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of establishing and comforting believers in their faith. They highlight the role of leaders in strengthening the community and encouraging perseverance through challenges.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
