(52, 3, 3, 44, 14, 22, 22, 'these afflictions', 'Afflictions and Tribulation Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the inevitability of suffering for believers. 1 Thessalonians speaks of being ''appointed'' to afflictions, while Acts highlights that ''through much tribulation'' one enters the kingdom.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 3, 3, 45, 5, 3, 3, 'these afflictions', 'Afflictions and Tribulations Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of afflictions and tribulations in the believer''s life. 1 Thessalonians speaks of being appointed to afflictions, while Romans highlights glorying in tribulations, indicating a shared understanding of their purpose in developing patience.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 3, 3, 44, 9, 16, 16, 'appointed thereunto', 'Suffering for Faith Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of suffering for faith. In 1 Thessalonians, believers are reminded that they are ''appointed'' to face afflictions, while Acts speaks of the suffering that will come for following Christ.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 3, 3, 43, 16, 33, 33, 'appointed thereunto', 'Affliction and Overcoming', 'Both passages emphasize the reality of tribulation in the world and the assurance of overcoming it. 1 Thessalonians speaks to being appointed to afflictions, while John offers peace through Christ''s victory over the world.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 3, 3, 46, 15, 58, 58, 'that no man should be moved', 'Afflictions and Steadfastness', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of being steadfast in the face of challenges. 1 Thessalonians encourages believers not to be moved by afflictions, while 1 Corinthians calls for steadfastness in the work of the Lord despite difficulties.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(52, 3, 3, 40, 10, 16, 18, 'appointed thereunto', 'Afflictions and Persecution', 'Both passages emphasize the inevitability of afflictions and persecution faced by believers. In 1 Thessalonians, it is stated that believers are ''appointed'' to these challenges, while Matthew warns of being delivered up to councils and scourged.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
